/2017/10/03/arts/onora-oneill-berggruen-prize.html\">\"Onora O'Neill Wins $1 Million Berggruen Prize for Philosophy\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_New_York_Times\" title=\"The New York Times\">The New York Times</a></i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Onora+O%E2%80%99Neill+Wins+%241+Million+Berggruen+Prize+for+Philosophy&amp;rft.date=2017-10-03&amp;rft.au=Jennifer+Schuessler&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2017%2F10%2F03%2Farts%2Fonora-oneill-berggruen-prize.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Berggruen+Prize\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Berggruen_Prize&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><span class=\"official-website\"><span class=\"url\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://berggruen.org/prize\">Official website</a></span></span></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o6-UcVX8Fto&amp;list=PLyYCSKWs8iYhxJzATF5z6Owzp_O9CIwx_\">Berggruen Prize Winner Charles Taylor on the Big Questions</a>; series of videos produced by the <a href=\"/wiki/Berggruen_Institute\" title=\"Berggruen Institute\">Berggruen Institute</a> on occasion of Charles Taylor winning the inaugural prize.</li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iN0FMBgY7rU\">The Berggruen Prize</a>; commentary of Berggruen Prize jurors such as <a href=\"/wiki/Amy_Gutmann\" title=\"Amy Gutmann\">Amy Gutmann</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Antonio_Damasio\" title=\"Antonio Damasio\